FBIS3-47846 "dreas011_d_94018" FBIS-EAS-94-011 Document Type:Daily Report 18 Jan 1994 South Korea Government Questions Russia SK1801032594 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 2330 GMT 18 Jan 94 SK1801032594 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network Language: Korean Article Type:BFN [Text] The government has asked Russia whether the recent foreign news report stating that it has decided to sell additional submarines to North Korea is true. Paek Nak-wan, director-general for the European Affairs Bureau of the Foreign Ministry, called a Russian minister to the ROK to the Foreign Ministry today and asked him to reveal whether the foreign news report stating that Russia had sold the four Fox-Trot submarines to North Korea and that it has recently concluded a contract to sell 10 additional Golf-class submarines to North Korea is true.
